-- guide_places: editorial rich text (take_title + body markdown) for all places, brand voice
update guide_places set take_title=E'where a *slow morning* turns into brunch, work, and then cocktails.', body=E'milevskii is a specialty coffee spot that quietly does everything. **strong breakfast menu, fresh bakery, all-day brunch**, and by evening it''s pouring cocktails and wine. the interior is *stylish but still cozy* \u2014 closer to an all-day coffee bar than a classic caf\u00e9.\n\nit works for whatever your day is doing: a slow morning, a few hours of remote work, or meeting a friend. people come for the **beautifully presented brunch** \u2014 syrniki, benedicts, filter coffee \u2014 and tend to stay.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* specialty coffee\n* breakfast & brunch\n* desserts & bakery\n* working remotely\n* relaxed meetings\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* syrniki\n* salmon benedict\n* flat white\n* filter coffee\n* pastries & desserts\n\n6 irakli abashidze st, batumi. daily **09:00 \u2013 20:00**. pet-friendly. **\u224820\u201330 \u20be**.' where slug='milevskii-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *filter coffee* when we''re tired of the boulevard.', body=E'most coffee in batumi is fine. some of it is bad. **nova is in a different category** \u2014 third-wave, single-origin, properly roasted, served with the patience of someone who knows what they''re doing.\n\nthe morning is for **pour-over, not espresso**. they rotate ethiopian and colombian regularly; ask what''s on the manual brew bar today. you can have it sweet *(filter brings out the fruit)* or smooth *(V60 if you want clarity)*. a flat white runs **\u224812 \u20be**, filter **\u224814 \u20be**.\n\nthe room itself is clean and unfussy: *tile, wood, two small tables, a window onto the street.* not the place for a long lunch \u2014 but the perfect place for two hours of reading, an interview, or a quiet first coffee before the city wakes up.\n\nthey bake their own croissants on fridays. by saturday they''re trying. by sunday they''re gone. **if you see a croissant after 11am, take it.**\n\nparnavaz mepe 60. every day 08:00 \u2013 23:00.' where slug='nova-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we drive out of town for *dinner by the sea* and stay for the breeze.', body=E'elly is a poolside restaurant in gonio, a short drive from batumi, doing **european cooking with georgian accents** plus cocktails and wine. it''s the quieter side of the coast \u2014 *greenery, a terrace, the breeze* \u2014 and it feels like leaving the city without really leaving it.\n\nwe come here to slow down: **breakfast by the sea**, a long sunset dinner, or a wine evening on the terrace. seafood and the breakfast menu are the easy choices.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* breakfast & brunch\n* sunset dinners\n* wine & cocktails\n* slow weekends outside batumi\n* relaxed evenings by the sea\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* european dishes with georgian accents\n* cocktails & wine\n* seafood\n* breakfast menu\n* desserts\n\ngonio, 18 andria pirveltsodebuli hwy III deadlock. daily **09:00 \u2013 21:00**. **\u224830\u201370 \u20be**.' where slug='elly-restaurant-gonio';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go when the supermarket shelf *isn''t enough*.', body=E'alcobrand is **one of the most popular alcohol stores in batumi**, with a big selection of *georgian and imported wines, whiskey, gin, tequila, beer, and premium spirits*. a good stop when you want something beyond the typical supermarket pick.\n\nthree locations: 98 zurab gorgiladze st, 25 zurab gorgiladze st, and 12 mikheil lermontovi, batumi.' where slug='alcobrand';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we find the *cheese and wine* the city otherwise hides.', body=E'gastronome calls itself **the first gourmet store chain in georgia** \u2014 a gourmet grocery and delicatessen with a *carefully selected collection of european products, wine, cheese, snacks, and desserts.* the kind of specialty food that''s **hard to find elsewhere in batumi**.\n\n14 vazha-pshavela st, batumi.' where slug='gastronome-batumi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we taste *qvevri wine* from wineries you''ve never heard of.', body=E'8000 vintages is a modern **wine shop and bar** and one of the best places in batumi to get into georgian wine. the focus is *small georgian wineries* \u2014 **natural and qvevri wines** from across the country.\n\ngood for both buying a bottle and drinking one on the spot. batumi, gogebashvili 30.' where slug='8000-vintages';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where the bartender remembers your drink and *builds you a new one*.', body=E'qube is a small, **very atmospheric cocktail bar** that feels more like a local spot than a tourist bar \u2014 *cozy interior, friendly bartenders, no club energy.* the kind of place people come back to for conversation, music, and **really well-made drinks**.\n\nit works to start the night or to stay until late. ask for a classic or let them **build a custom cocktail to your taste**.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* cocktails & nightlife\n* late-night drinks\n* relaxed atmosphere\n* meeting friends\n* starting the night in batumi\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* signature cocktails\n* negroni\n* daiquiri\n* espresso martini\n* custom cocktails based on your taste\n\n4 sherif khimshiashvili st, batumi. daily **20:00 \u2013 05:00**. **\u224820\u201370 \u20be**.' where slug='qube-bar';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where a *slow morning* gets a good flat white and a pastry.', body=E'livi is a cozy modern caf\u00e9 built around **specialty coffee, fresh pastries, and desserts**. it''s become one of the local go-tos in batumi for *breakfasts, coffee meetings, and slow mornings* \u2014 good food and beautifully made drinks.\n\nkldiashvili 16, batumi. open daily **09:00 \u2013 22:00**. **\u224810\u201320 \u20be**.' where slug='livi-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we order a *classic cocktail* and let the night run long.', body=E'gimlet is one of batumi''s best cocktail bars for people who care about **classic drinks, good music, and a stylish but relaxed room**. modern bar culture with a *cozy european feel*.\n\nit works both ways: a **quiet evening cocktail** or the start of a longer night out.\n\n17 zviad gamsakhurdia st, batumi 6010. daily **18:00 \u2013 03:00**. **\u224820\u201360 \u20be**.' where slug='gimlet-bar';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *full recovery day* near the beach.', body=E'**one of the biggest SPA spaces in batumi**, near new boulevard. indoor pool, hammam, sauna, massage treatments and a fitness floor \u2014 enough to fill a whole day.\n\nthe big draw is *sea views and room to breathe*. you can move between the water, the heat and the massage table without ever feeling cramped.\n\n**a full recovery and wellness day near the beach** is the honest pitch here.\n\n3 lech and maria kaczynski st, batumi\n\ndaily: 09:00 \u2013 23:00' where slug='grand-bellagio-wellness-spa';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *stylish dinner* away from the tourist crowd.', body=E'modern georgian inside the radisson blu hotel \u2014 **classic georgian flavors with a more refined contemporary style**. one of the better calls in batumi for a stylish dinner, wine, and a calmer room away from the typical tourist restaurants.\n\nthe interior is *modern and sophisticated*; the menu mixes classic georgian dishes with european presentation. **in summer the terrace is one of the nicest spots for long dinners and evening wine.**\n\nperfect for:\n\n* elegant dinners\n* georgian cuisine with a modern twist\n* wine & cocktails\n* date nights\n* business meetings\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* adjarian khachapuri\n* khinkali\n* grilled meat dishes\n* georgian wine\n* desserts\n\nninoshvili st. 1, radisson blu hotel, batumi\n\ndaily: 13:00 \u2013 00:00' where slug='medea-restaurant';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *slow wellness day* by the boulevard.', body=E'a wellness floor inside radisson blu batumi, right by the boulevard and old batumi. *panoramic sea views*, indoor pool, fitness center, sauna and steam room \u2014 **one of the best options in the city for a slower wellness day**.\n\nthe signature here is **anne semonin treatments**, plus a calm room to do nothing in for a few hours.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* SPA & wellness\n* indoor pool\n* sauna & steam room\n* relaxing massages\n* slow living\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* anne semonin treatments\n* indoor pool access\n* sauna & steam room\n* relaxing massage\n* a wellness day with sea views\n\n1 ninoshvili st, batumi\n\ndaily' where slug='radisson-blu-batumi-spa';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *classic brasserie dinner* in old batumi.', body=E'a **european-style brasserie in the heart of old batumi** \u2014 *elegant interiors, classic atmosphere*, one of the more refined dinners in the city.\n\nit takes after traditional french and european brasseries: **timeless design, wine culture, and carefully prepared dishes**.\n\n25 memed abashidze ave, batumi' where slug='brasserie-1900';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *slow mornings* away from the city.', body=E'a quiet caf\u00e9 built around **specialty coffee and signature breakfasts**. *minimalist design, soft natural light, small curated details* \u2014 it reads more like a calm creative space than a regular caf\u00e9.\n\nthis is a **slow-morning and brunch place**. it works equally well for conversations, working remotely, or just taking a break from the city.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* specialty coffee\n* signature breakfasts\n* brunch & desserts\n* working remotely\n* slow mornings\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* breakfast dishes\n* specialty coffee\n* desserts\n* signature drinks\n\ndavid mamuladze 19, batumi\n\ndaily: 09:00 \u2013 23:00' where slug='moonrise';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *all-day food* and trendy drinks.', body=E'a **stylish all-day caf\u00e9** with a modern interior and *a relaxed atmosphere that makes you stay longer than planned*.\n\nravi leans on **trendy drinks, good food and music** \u2014 fresh and modern without trying too hard. expect to spend **\u224820\u201350 \u20be**.\n\n27 mamuladze st, next white\n\ndaily: 10:00 \u2013 22:00' where slug='ravi-neobistro';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *fresh pastries* and a reliable morning.', body=E'**one of batumi''s cozy everyday spots** for good coffee, fresh pastries, and relaxed breakfasts. *warm atmosphere, quality bakery, simple but consistently good food.*\n\n**open since 2019**, with a loyal local following to show for it.\n\nkhariton akhvlediani, 4a\n\nmon\u2013fri: 8:30 \u2013 21:00\n\nsat\u2013sun: 9:00 \u2013 21:00' where slug='rhino-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *sushi at sunset* above the city.', body=E'a japanese restaurant **on the 33rd floor**, with *panoramic views over the sea, mountains, and the batumi skyline*. authentic japanese cuisine, cocktails and sake \u2014 it feels very different from the typical sushi places in town.\n\nit''s a **collaboration between panorama restaurant, ORBI group and ginza project**, with chef ri focused on authentic dishes and good ingredients. *natural wood, plants, soft lighting* inside; **evening DJ sets and sunset views** outside.\n\nperfect for:\n\n* sushi & sashimi\n* sunset dinners\n* cocktails & sake\n* date nights\n* stylish evenings\n\nwhat to try:\n\n* sashimi & nigiri\n* signature rolls\n* kaisen don\n* japanese cocktails\n* sake selection\n\n15b sherif khimshiashvili st, 33rd floor, batumi\n\nsun\u2013fri: 15:00 \u2013 00:00\n\nsat: 15:00 \u2013 01:00' where slug='japan-33';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *quiet mornings* off the tourist streets.', body=E'a calm, well-designed caf\u00e9 built on **specialty coffee and slow breakfasts**. *simple, good coffee, a relaxed room.*\n\nit''s become **one of batumi''s favorite spots for quiet mornings** away from the busy tourist streets.\n\nlermontov st. 8\n\ndaily: 09:00 \u2013 22:00' where slug='minimalist-coffee-and-food';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we settle in with a laptop and a *flat white* and somehow stay all day', body=E'a cozy modern caf\u00e9 that does **specialty coffee and european comfort food** in one of those neighborhood spots that just works. it''s on inasaridze 13, open *8:00 to 22:00*, and yes, **pet friendly**.\n\nwhat we like is that it covers the whole day. breakfast, lunch, *coffee with a laptop*, or a slow evening with wine and friends \u2014 it holds up for all of it.\n\nprice: \u224810\u201320 \u20be.' where slug='nord-specialty-coffee-food';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where the specialty-coffee people went next, this time with *wine and long brunches*', body=E'a modern bistro from the people behind one of batumi''s favorite specialty coffee spots \u2014 but **a completely new format**. this time it''s a proper bistro: *beautiful interior, warm natural light*, wine, cocktails, and a relaxed european feel.\n\nit''s built for **long brunches and slow dinners** with friends. breakfast, lunch, coffee, wine, pastries \u2014 all of it is on the table.\n\nhours: mon\u2013fri 9:00\u201322:59, sat\u2013sun 9:00\u201323:59. find it at 26 may, 20. price: \u224820\u201330 \u20be.' where slug='pure-bistro';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *slow breakfast* that turns into evening drinks', body=E'an **all-day caf\u00e9 and bar** with a relaxed feel, good music, and *one of the nicest modern interiors* in batumi. cocktails, brunches, slow breakfasts \u2014 it shifts gears through the day.\n\nit''s the kind of place we pick for **meeting friends** and evening drinks. you can come early or stay late.\n\nhours: everyday 11am\u201311pm, friday\u2013saturday 11am\u201312am. at 39 noe zhordania st.' where slug='nisha';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we end the night over *vinyl and jazz* in the dim light', body=E'one of batumi''s most atmospheric cocktail bars, built in the spirit of a **classic european speakeasy**. *dim lighting, vinyl music, jazz*, and cocktails that are actually made with care.\n\nthe feeling lands somewhere between tbilisi, berlin, and old odessa. craft drinks and bites.\n\nhours: open 18:00\u201302:00, kitchen till 00:00. at 14 zviad gamsakhurdia st. price: \u224810\u201340 \u20be.' where slug='1905-bar';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we time dinner to the *sunset* over the old town and the port', body=E'a **rooftop restaurant** above rooms batumi, set poolside with *360\u00b0 views over the old town and the port*. the menu is built around **local seafood and smart vegetarian plates**, with a considered list of georgian and international wines, and cocktails mixed at the rooftop bar.\n\nit''s open for dinner, so we time it for sunset and stay for the skyline.\n\nwhat we order: go classic with a **seafood main and a glass of georgian wine** \u2014 or keep it lighter with a vegetarian plate and a cocktail from the bar. an easy, unhurried way to take in the view and the room.\n\nwhere: rooftop of rooms batumi.' where slug='the-kitchen-by-rooms';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *handmade khinkali* after a walk along the boulevard', body=E'a city-center spot for **simple, honest georgian classics** with no fuss. cozy and casual, but the real reason to come is the dish they''re known for: *handmade khinkali \u2014 juicy, generously filled, served piping hot*.\n\nthere''s a short menu of comfort plates, **local wine by the glass**, and a smooth house chacha to match.\n\nwhat we order: a full plate of classic khinkali (our pick here) with a *shot of chacha* \u2014 or keep it light with a glass of local wine. it''s the easiest way to taste why locals come back late after a seaside walk.\n\ngood to know: central location, friendly service, and **late hours** \u2014 handy for an unplanned, no-frills dinner after the boulevard. price: \u224820\u201370 \u20be.' where slug='daphna-batumi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we come for *italian cooking* and stay for the creme brulee', body=E'a restaurant in a *scenic spot by the seafront*, cozy and elegant, with views of the city from every angle. it feels less like a night out and more like **a special occasion** every time.\n\nthe kitchen is known for its **italian cuisine** \u2014 fresh ingredients, classic pasta and risotto, salads, and meat dishes. but the one to remember is the *creme brulee*: creamy custard under a crunchy caramel crust.\n\nthe **wine list** is serious too, with fine italian bottles and gems from elsewhere, and a sommelier who''ll help you pair. the staff take care of you, and the whole place feels warm and welcoming.\n\nhours: 12:00\u201300:00, kitchen until 23:00. whatsapp +995 555 77 44 88. near the old dancing fountain, seafront promenade, batumi.' where slug='ambassadori-restaurant';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we order *sweet hokkaido toast* with a batch brew and call it breakfast', body=E'a city-center caf\u00e9 with **really good coffee from roasters in saudi arabia**. they specialize in breakfast \u2014 *hokkaido toast, english breakfast*, and a few original dishes. for coffee there''s a classic menu or you can try different brewing methods.\n\nwhat we order: the **sweet hokkaido toast** with a freshly made batch brew.\n\nspecial offer for guests of the BRE apartments: show the BRE.GE CLUB logo and **get your coffee for free** when you order any meal.\n\nhours: 9am to 6pm. at 40, melikishvili str.' where slug='urban-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go big for a *georgian feast* a hundred meters above the sea', body=E'the **largest restaurant complex in adjara**, with open kitchens *one hundred meters above sea level*. it''s a multi-level project by ginza project, with a **360-degree view**, dynamic terraces, and cuisine by the first georgian chef recognized by the michelin guide.\n\nit sits across **four floors in the central ORBI sea tower**, each level with its own atmosphere drawn from georgian culture. with izo dzandzava in the kitchen, it''s meant to feel like *a colorful, generous georgian feast* \u2014 whether you''re with a hundred friends or on a date for two. the menu runs through the classics, recipes passed down in the dzandzava family, with room for creative interpretations.\n\nexpect open kitchens, high-level service, and a **collection of rare georgian wines**. this is the creators'' vision of where georgian restaurant culture is heading \u2014 scale like this is a first for batumi.\n\nhours: 11:00\u201300:00. menu by izo dzandzava. +995 598 42 42 42. at 15B, sherif khimshiashvili str.' where slug='panorama-restaurant';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we send people who want georgian food with a *european accent*', body=E'one of the coolest restaurants in town. modern **georgian cuisine with a touch of europe**, and they go a little crazy for asian food too.\n\nit''s a really good place with *awesome food* \u2014 the kind of spot where you can have a proper night out. sometimes there''s **live music**.\n\nthe chef, @mamiajojua, is marked by the michelin guide. open mon\u2013sun 10:00\u201300:00, at 1 lech and maria kaczynski str. +995 577 294 680.' where slug='g-garden-restaurant';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *khachapuri and khinkali* in the middle of the city', body=E'a restaurant in the heart of the city with **authentic georgian food**. you can taste all the real georgian flavors here: *khachapuri, khinkali, ajapsandali*, and more.\n\nthe place often has **live music**, and there''s *outdoor seating on the terrace* when the weather is right.\n\ncuisine is georgian and european. it sits at the intersection of vakhtang gorgasali and haidar abashidze streets. roughly 20\u201370 \u20be.' where slug='tiflis';
update guide_places set take_title=E'the cafe everyone in batumi seems to end up at *eventually*', body=E'pure is maybe the **most popular cafe in batumi**. it works for breakfast, dinner, and getting work done.\n\nthe *branded breakfasts* run until 7 p.m., and the coffee is excellent. there''s also **wine by the glass** plus salads and snacks.\n\nopen every day 9:00\u201322:00, with delivery. at 8 lech and maria kaczynski str. roughly 20\u201330 \u20be.' where slug='pure-coffee';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we work when we want *old batumi* out the window', body=E'a coworking and creative workspace inside rooms batumi, in the heart of **old batumi near the sea**. modern design, comfortable work areas, and *fast Wi-Fi*.\n\nit leans toward freelancers, designers, entrepreneurs, and remote workers who want a more *aesthetic, relaxed* place to work.\n\nat 10 gogebashvili st. open 24/7.' where slug='d-block-workspace-rooms-batumi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'the central coworking where we go to *actually meet people*', body=E'a modern coworking and creative workspace in the **center of batumi**, built for freelancers, startups, remote workers, and digital nomads.\n\nyou get comfortable work areas, *fast Wi-Fi*, meeting rooms, and a community feel \u2014 plus **regular networking events**, which is the real reason to pick it.\n\nat 37 memed abashidze ave. open daily.' where slug='terminal-coworking';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we work when we want our desk *near the boulevard*', body=E'a modern coworking space near new boulevard and the sea, popular with freelancers, remote workers, startups, and digital nomads. a *relaxed atmosphere*, fast Wi-Fi, meeting rooms, quiet zones, and a real **remote-work community**.\n\nit''s an easy pick if you''re staying near the boulevard and want a **calm, productive spot** close to caf\u00e9s, restaurants, and the beach.\n\nwhat''s here:\n* open-space desks\n* fixed workplaces\n* meeting rooms\n* quiet zones\n* tea & coffee\n* flexible daily and monthly passes\n\ngood for: remote work, freelancers & startups, *laptop-friendly* workdays, networking, and working near the sea.\n\nat 4 sherif khimshiashvili st. daily 10:00\u201322:00.' where slug='lendspace';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go on a *rainy day* when the beach is out', body=E'a modern wellness complex near new boulevard, close to the sea. it brings together an **indoor pool**, finnish sauna, hammam, massage treatments, and fitness facilities. one of the most *well-designed SPA spaces* in batumi, used by hotel guests and locals alike.\n\nsoft modern interiors, large relaxation areas, and a comfortable pool zone that works especially well on *rainy days, recovery days, or quiet evenings after the beach*.\n\nwhat to try:\n* relaxing massage\n* hammam session\n* finnish sauna\n* indoor pool access\n* wellness treatments & recovery programs\n\ngood for: SPA & wellness, indoor pool, hammam & sauna, massage & recovery, and **wellness weekends near the sea**.\n\nat 5a lech and maria kaczynski st. daily 08:00\u201323:00.' where slug='orchid-spa-batumi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'the hilton SPA we book for a proper *recovery day*', body=E'a SPA inside hilton batumi, just steps from the boulevard and the sea. one of the **best-known wellness spaces** in the city, with indoor pool access, sauna, steam room, massages, and fitness facilities in a *calm setting*.\n\nit''s popular for recovery days, rainy weather, and slower **wellness-focused weekends**.\n\ntreatments include classic massages, *hot stone therapy*, vichy shower procedures, facials, and wellness rituals built for relaxation and reset.\n\nat 40 rustaveli ave. daily 09:00\u201322:00.' where slug='eforea-spa-at-hilton-batumi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go when we want the *five-star* version of a spa day', body=E'shine SPA at sheraton batumi is one of the city''s best-known wellness spaces, mixing **classic hotel elegance** with a full SPA setup. there''s an indoor pool, jacuzzi, sauna, steam room, fitness facilities, and treatment rooms.\n\nit''s built for *slower recovery days* and calm evenings near the boulevard.\n\nwhat to try:\n* relaxing massage\n* jacuzzi & indoor pool\n* sauna & steam room\n* wellness treatments\n* a *spa evening after the beach*\n\ngood for: SPA & wellness, indoor pool & jacuzzi, sauna & steam room, relaxation, and **rainy day recovery**.\n\nat 28 rustaveli ave. open daily.' where slug='sheraton-batumi-shine-spa';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a full *slow-living* day by the sea near new boulevard', body=E'a large seaside wellness complex in new boulevard with **indoor and outdoor pools**, sauna, steam room, massage treatments, gym, and **direct beach access**. one of the most popular SPA options in batumi for a full relaxing day by the sea.\n\nthe hotel is especially known for its big indoor pool area, heated pool, outdoor seasonal pool, wellness zone, and *panoramic sea views*. works well both for quick recovery days and full slow-living weekends near the beach.\n\nperfect for:\n* SPA & wellness\n* indoor & outdoor pools\n* sauna & steam room\n* massage & recovery\n* seaside relaxation\n\nwhat to try:\n* indoor heated pool\n* sauna & steam room\n* relaxing massage\n* outdoor pool in summer\n* spa day with sea views\n\n18 sherif khimshiashvili st, batumi\n\ndaily: 08:00 \u2013 22:00' where slug='colosseum-marina-spa';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *calm* spa day in the center when it rains', body=E'a wellness and SPA space in the center of old batumi with **indoor and outdoor pools**, sauna, steam room, massages, fitness area, and *panoramic sea views*. one of the better options in the city for a slower wellness day near the boulevard and the beach.\n\nthe hotel''s explore spa is especially known for its **calm atmosphere**, modern design, pool area, and massage treatments.\n\nperfect for:\n* SPA & wellness\n* indoor pool\n* sauna & steam room\n* rainy day relaxation\n* slow living\n\nwhat to try:\n* relaxing massage\n* sauna & steam room\n* indoor pool access\n* wellness treatments\n* spa day with sea views\n\nninoshvili / zhgenti street, batumi\n\ndaily: 07:00 \u2013 23:00' where slug='le-m-ridien-batumi-spa-wellness';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we grab a scooter for the *short hop* between caf\u00e9 and beach', body=E'JETJET is an electric scooter sharing service in batumi that works through a mobile app with **QR-based unlocking** and *flexible per-minute pricing*.\n\nwe use it for short rides between caf\u00e9s, beaches, coworking spaces, and central areas of the city without needing taxis or rental cars.' where slug='jet-scooter-rent';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we ride when we want the *cheapest* car across town', body=E'taxi maxim is a **budget-friendly ride-hailing service** in batumi and other cities across georgia.\n\nthe app is popular among locals and long-term visitors thanks to *lower prices* than other taxi platforms and a simple ride ordering process. taximaxim.com' where slug='maxim-taxi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we tap for a ride at *almost any hour* of the day', body=E'yandex go is one of the most widely used ride-hailing apps in batumi for everyday transportation, airport rides, late-night trips, and moving around the city without a rental car. it works through a mobile app with **upfront pricing**, live driver tracking, and multiple ride categories depending on comfort and budget.\n\nwe use it most for *affordable rides* between new boulevard, old batumi, beaches, coworking spaces, restaurants, and nightlife areas. you can **pay by card or cash** and order rides at almost any time of day.\n\nperfect for:\n* airport transfers\n* affordable city rides\n* nightlife transportation\n* moving around batumi without a car\n* everyday transportation\n\nwhat to expect:\n* app-based ride ordering\n* upfront pricing\n* card & cash payments\n* multiple ride categories\n* 24/7 availability\n\navailable across batumi via mobile app\n\n24/7' where slug='yandex-go-taxi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we tap first for a ride, the *main* app everyone uses here', body=E'bolt is the main ride-hailing service used in batumi for everyday city transportation, airport trips, late-night rides, and moving around without a rental car.\n\nthe app works much like uber and is widely used by **locals and tourists** thanks to its simple interface, *fast pickup times*, and affordable pricing.' where slug='bolt-taxi';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we grab a car for a *spontaneous* trip without the rental office', body=E'getmancar is an app-based carsharing service in batumi for quick city trips, flexible daily rentals, and spontaneous travel around the city **without paperwork or rental offices**.\n\ncars can be booked, *unlocked, and managed* directly through the getmancar mobile app.' where slug='getmancar-carsharing';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we rent a car for the *coast and the mountains*', body=E'easyrent is a car rental service in batumi with flexible options for travelers heading out to the city, the coastline, and the mountain regions of georgia.\n\nit''s popular with tourists and digital nomads thanks to an **easy booking process**, *well-maintained cars*, and customer-oriented service.\n\n98 zurab gorgiladze st, batumi' where slug='easyrent-car-rental';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we rent a car with *no deposit* and unlimited mileage', body=E'a local car rental service in batumi with practical, flexible options for travelers heading out to the city, the coast, and the mountain regions of georgia. handy for anyone who wants **simple rental conditions**, affordable pricing, and easy communication without a complicated booking process.\n\nthe service offers city cars, SUVs, and vehicles for longer trips around georgia, with *unlimited mileage options* and **no-deposit cars** available for selected vehicles. works for short batumi stays and long road trips alike.\n\nperfect for:\n* road trips around georgia\n* mountain & coastal travel\n* affordable daily rentals\n* flexible rental conditions\n* independent travel around batumi\n\nwhat to expect:\n* unlimited mileage\n* no-deposit car options\n* booking without prepayment\n* affordable pricing\n* local support\n\ncars from 80 GEL' where slug='vasily-car-rental';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we rent a car when we want to *leave batumi* and drive the rest of georgia', body=E'geo.drive is a car rental service in batumi with one of the largest fleets in the city \u2014 economy, comfort, SUVs, and premium. they do *airport delivery*, flexible pickup, and **24/7 support**, so you''re covered whenever you land or need to swap plans.\n\nwhere it really earns its keep is **road trips outside batumi** \u2014 mountain regions, wineries, beaches, and the smaller coastal towns. they also do *one-way rentals between cities*, with pickup and return options across batumi, tbilisi, kutaisi, and the airports.\n\nbeyond rental they also handle investments, buying, and auto service.\n\nperfect for:\n* road trips around georgia\n* airport pickup\n* long-term rental\n* mountain & coastal travel\n* flexible intercity travel\n\nwhat to expect:\n* insured vehicles\n* 24/7 support\n* airport delivery\n* one-way rental options\n* economy to premium cars\n\n90 lermontov str, batumi (also 220 airport highway). open 24/7.' where slug='geo-drive-car-rental';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *slow sunset dinner* once we''re done with the city center', body=E'botanico sits near the batumi botanical garden out at green cape, surrounded by *greenery and sea views*. it feels more like a coastal escape than a city restaurant \u2014 the kind of place for slow lunches, sunset dinners, and **long conversations with wine**.\n\nthe kitchen mixes **georgian and european cooking**, and there''s a poolside atmosphere with cocktails and *panoramic views of the black sea*. one of the better spots around batumi when you want a relaxed dinner away from the busy center.\n\nperfect for:\n* sunset dinners\n* wine & cocktails\n* food with a sea view\n* slow weekends outside the city\n* special occasions\n\nwhat to try:\n* georgian & european dishes\n* seafood\n* cocktails\n* wine selection\n* desserts\n\ngreen cape, near batumi botanical garden. daily 12:00 \u2013 00:00.' where slug='botanico-cafe';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we drink *natural qvevri wine* in a converted family garage', body=E'garage wines is a natural wine bar and shop set inside a **former family garage in old batumi**. it''s one of the most atmospheric places in town for georgian natural, organic, and biodynamic wines, in a setting that stays relaxed and honest.\n\nit feels like a local gathering spot more than a wine bar \u2014 *vintage interiors, wine cellars, candlelight*, cheese, and a team that genuinely loves wine. people come not just to drink but to **learn about georgian winemaking** and try small producers you rarely find elsewhere.\n\nperfect for:\n* natural georgian wines\n* wine & cheese evenings\n* authentic local atmosphere\n* date nights\n* slow conversations and late evenings\n\nwhat to try:\n* natural qvevri wines\n* cheese plates\n* georgian biodynamic wines\n* homemade desserts\n* local tea & chacha\n\n8 giorgi mazniashvili st, batumi. daily 18:00 \u2013 00:00; weekends until 01:00. roughly 10\u201340 \u20be.' where slug='garage-wines-wine-bar';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we settle in with a laptop for a *slow morning* in the old town', body=E'nord is one of the **most loved specialty coffee spots** in batumi, with a *minimalist scandinavian-style interior* and a calm atmosphere. good coffee, and a good place to slow down.\n\nit works for slow mornings, **working from a laptop**, or just taking a break from the city. *pet friendly*, too.\n\n24 noe zhordania st, batumi. every day 10:00 \u2013 22:00.' where slug='nord-coffee-old-town';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for *filter coffee* and a bag of beans to take home', body=E'kopi brew is a **specialty coffee roastery and shop** \u2014 one of the best spots in batumi for people who actually love coffee. they *roast their own beans* and serve excellent filter coffee and espresso.\n\nthe atmosphere feels more like a local european caf\u00e9 than a touristy place. good for a relaxed breakfast, or **buying beans to take home**.\n\nperfect for:\n* morning coffee\n* working with a laptop\n* a relaxed breakfast\n* buying beans to take home\n\n8 lermontov st. 09:00 \u2013 22:00.' where slug='kopi-brew';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where the *brand barista* who won championships pulls our coffee', body=E'kava lova is a cozy caf\u00e9 in the heart of the city that **started as a little coffee shop**. it''s run by brand barista @ekaterina_kostenko, a participant and *winner of coffee championships*.\n\nthe staff are experts who love coffee, and it shows. you can get **amazing specialty coffee** here, have lunch, drink some wine, and try *desserts they make themselves*.\n\n31 zubalashvili str. every day 10:00 \u2013 21:00. roughly 10\u201320 \u20be.' where slug='kava-lova';
update guide_places set take_title=E'where we go for a *calm reset day* without leaving the city', body=E'gardenia spa sits inside STEPS batumi hotel & suites, close to new boulevard and the sea. it''s a **relaxed spa and wellness space** \u2014 a good option for a *calm reset day* without going anywhere.\n\nyou get massage, **sauna and steam room**, fitness facilities, and pool access *all in one place*.\n\n2b grigol lortkipanidze st, batumi. open daily.' where slug='gardenia-spa-at-steps-batumi';